[{"id":"VR857481","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a vertical convex mirror facing to the left with its principal axis shown as a dash line to the left of the mirror. A vertical arrow pointing up from the principal axis is labeled Object and it is at distance d sub o from the mirror.  A note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857481.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An object is located in front of a convex mirror, as shown in the figure. The object is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub o\"><math alttext=\"d sub o\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi>o</mi></msub></math></span></span> from the mirror, resulting in an image that is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub i\"><math alttext=\"d sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span></span> from the mirror. What is the orientation of the image, and what is the magnitude of the focal length of the mirror? Note that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub o\"><math alttext=\"d sub o\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi>o</mi></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d sub i\"><math alttext=\"d sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span></span> are both taken to be positive quantities.</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:30\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:90\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:110\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:co